Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses communication technologies and their reliability in a smart grid, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes a diversity combining scheme and evaluates its performance, which is related to information theory. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with the design and evaluation of a real-time testbed, which involves system and control aspects. 
4. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper may touch upon security aspects of smart grid communications, which falls under the scope of cryptography and security. 
5. cs.CY (Computers and Society) - The paper may discuss the societal impact of smart grid communications, which falls under the scope of computers and society.
